76561198010240963,Recommended,301120,31301682,Posted: 22 April,all,Chilidipped,"I  don't often write reviews, but I feel like this game deserves it.I've played a lot of sports simulation and strategy games and I have to tell you that this game REALLY deserves positve endorsement.  It performs at a level well beyond what you would expect given the level of minimal development resources its clearly been given.1) The AI is extraordinary - you really have to plan and have a clear, well-executed strategy to be able to compete at a high level consistently year after year in this game.  If you make mistakes in player acquisition or tactically mismatch you players to your approach game in and game out, you'll see yourself drafting Top 52) The modding community is committed and you get a lot for your money because of that3) THe UI, once you understand it and get used to its clunkiness, is actually pretty good - again for what little development has been done vs. what could be done.Remember, this is from the company that does Football Manager, so you can see the quality.  But, what disappoints is what this game could be if the developer gave it anywhere near the resources it gives FM.  And I hope as this game gets more following, they will listen.Regardless, don't pass this one up.  And for goodness sake, avoid FHM2 or FHM3 like the plaugue.  This game won't do stupid trades and it will give you some real immersion beause, as I said, the AI is good and difficult to beat.Enjoy!"
