,Recommended,301120,15124912,"Posted: 30 March, 2015",all,The Pied Piper,"DISCLAIMER: I want to start out by noting a couple of things that may be relevant to people interesed in this game. First, I never played Football Manager in any form, nor did I play this game's old 2007 iteration. I had no biases coming into this game. Second, while I am a hockey fan (Go Bolts!) I was not a hardcore fan. I was (and largely am) still fairly casual in that I don't follow mundane stats, am not up to date on every player in the league and don't watch every single game.That being said. This game is fantastic! I am having loads of fun with this gaming experience and as far as I can tell will be having lots of fun for months if not years to come.Who would like this game?- anyone who enjoys management games- anyone who enjoys stats and tactical games- any sports fans (hockey is a plus!)PROS:- addictive gameplay that makes you feel involved and responsible for your teams success and failure- a ""one more turn"" type of pull (days are done in turns)- a unique and highly realistic game simulator that you can watch in real time or sped up (highly entertaining)- HEAPS of potential, this game is still in Early Access but it is very fun and playable in it's current state, updates will only launch it to new heights- in depth stats and tactics including fully realized and modeled shot analysis for games (impressive)CONS:- confusing and unoptimized UI (needs streamlining)- can't control players yourself (this should go without saying but some people don't come to grips with this concept until they're in game)- lack of useful tutorial and helpful tooltips (had to bumble around some things before finding them out myself)- no sounds except crowd noise (might benefit from certain ambient sounds a calm musical track)All in all this game as it stands is great and will only continue to get better over time. It's a low price, can be played in short bursts or long stretches, has an addictive one more turn type of gameplay that makes you feel involved and connected to your team. I love it.8.5/10"
