,Recommended,301120,15197592,"Posted: 3 April, 2015",all,Vanilla,"An extremely in-depth version of GM Mode, I'm at September 9th, two days into the season and I have a headache from all the transactions and moves that I'm making, just like a GM would. Glad it's back and you'll all love this game if you buy it, worth every penny.Haven't found any glitches yet, but even if there are, it's Early Access so I'm sure they'll be fixed by then.Otherwise, really good potential for this game, very engaging and fun to play, and worth $16.99 CAD.Suggestion 1: Disallow players to put same players on the same line (Ex. Stamkos-Stamkos-Stamkos)Suggestion 2: Be able to mess with contracts a little bit. More flexibility (Ex. When player asks for 1.1 million a year, you should be able to offer him more or less depending on how he played last year)Suggestion 3: Remove having to name a different captain if current captain is injured. Takes too much time to rename temporary captain and rename regular captain after returning, and in the NHL today, we do not see this happening. Captains stay captains through the season.Edit 2 (November 15, 2015): Through ten years of my Tampa Bay GM Mode and winning the Cup a couple of times, there are just a few problems I've noticed that consistently occur.1. The AI in trading is an absolute travesty as of right now. It definitely could be worked on to be more balanced, perhaps like EA's NHL AI. As of now, the AI will trade each other ridiculous things like ""Dany Heatley and a 7th round pick for Patrick Kane, Jonathan Toews and a 1st round pick"", but when I try grabbing a player like Mike Green, they won't even take Stamkos for him, claiming to need just a little more. Definitely an irritating aspect that needs a little time to be worked on.2. Injuries, like EA's NHL, should have the option of being turned off at player's discretion. I've had a period of time where players such as Hedman, Stamkos, Vasilevskiy, and Drouin would all go out in the span of a week with major injuries that would take them out for 3 months or more. So for the future, either have the option to turn them off entirely, or fix it so such major injuries occur less frequently.3. A minor, miscellaneous problem with aesthetics I've noticed is the inability to ""expand your arena"" at all. It's a button there, but somehow despite my near-top attendance records season after season, it never seems to stop being grayed out. If it's there, I suggest a time when we could potentially expand our arena. Could be a cool little mini-feature, going into the future.4. Finally, player growth through practice really needs to be revamped. A player can spend 6 months on the practice screen as ""working on shooting"", but at the end of 4 years of that ""shooting practice"" their overall for that has not gone up at all. I'm not sure the logistics behind player growth, but I feel as though practice should be a factor in whether a player grows a certain stat or not.Through 10 years however, I have had little concern to doubt buying this game. An excellent pickup, which I am sure will please all hockey fans on PC even more when the game is fixed of its tiny bugs and glitches here and there.Edit 3 (December 31, 2015):Noticing a very disturbing trend that my goalies keep having extremely sub-par nights, despite their overall. Yes, I understand that every goalie has an off-night some nights, but I really don't think that a 5 star goalie such as Vasilievskiy can let in a combined total of 25 goals on 78 shots in 4 consecutive games, while this no-namer with red attributes shuts me out with ease in a 33 save effort. Going back to the ""practice"" screen, goalies working on their ""Goalie"" instructions should continue to grow more consistent and more capable of stopping pucks, and perhaps just going into the coding, tweak a couple of settings here and there."
