,Recommended,301120,15084556,"Posted: 27 March, 2015",all,Gr8one,"Although early access, EHM:EA is a very polished management simulation. If you enjoy hockey, or any sports gm games, you owe it yourself to pick this game up.From Version 15.0.1b (first early access version) here are some of my findings on the game:Pro's:- Has nearly all the features from the EHM 2007, meaning it already is the deepest hockey sim available.- Nice new touches like players bio information talking about players close friends on the team.- Nice tactical improvements like individual strategies for players-Tactical improvements for lines including choosing who would be the playmaker on the line.- Free Agency is much more realistic. Don't expect to always build your teams on July 1st, UFA's want money and term just ilke in real life.-Position's of players are more in-depth, including their roles like defensive defenseman, stay-at-home defensemen, 2-way forward, skilled forward, quick forward. This adds to the fun of building cohesive forward units.-Tons of international tournaments, take control of your favorite national team and try to build a team to bring glory to your country.-The in game match view has been improved and is very enjoyable watching your team battle it out.Con's:- Interface and menus are very similar to EHM 2007 so it is missing some more modern interface options.- Resolution needs to be improved for modern pc's- Scoring has to be balanced a bit more to 2015 scoring levels (its a bit too high at least in NHL games).- Missing leagues like the Swiss leagues, Russian MHL, and British Hockey leagues from 2007 version.- Coaches and GMs get fired a little more than in the real world.There are a few issues like the small window the game runs in and the interface definitely needs some modern touches, but the rest of the cons are minor. The positives far outweigh the negatives with this release. Please do yourself a favor and buy this game if you enjoy the sport of hockey and have ever wanted to build your dream team or test your management skill in the lower leagues and build a legendary story as you climb the ranks to finally leading your national team to world glory."
