,Recommended,301120,18496944,"Posted: 15 October, 2015",all,Gattsu,"I am addicted to this game, please somebody help me!Running the gamut, EHM takes what's good about Be A GM mode in EA's NHL series and turns it up a level. Despite the minimalistic animations of the game, which essentially consist of watching 10 dots with small sticks running around the ice,  the clear meat of the game is within the management aspect of the game, hence the title.From assigning individual scouts to scour specific countries, leagues, teams or even individual players, to keeping up to date and managing contracts on an annual basis. You will need to continuously conduct scouting missions in order to have information on upcoming prospects, if not, come the annual draft you will find yourself staring at barebone details regarding individual players. When it comes to contracts, be sure to re-sign and add free agents or claim players from waivers as needed, you'll regret it down the line if you forget to re negotiate with one of your star players.Players in EHM do not have a single 'overall' skill number and instead have over 25 different skills ranging from things like Slapshots, Flair, or Stamina. As well, the coaching staff, including physiotherapists are also ranked with a number of different skills.This is a great hockey management simulation, at a very reasonable price. However I almost wish I never discovered EHM, because now I have no life.10/10"
