,Recommended,301120,34698690,Posted: 2 September,all,Astrologist,"I've played this game for 2000+ hours and I must say for a simulation game, it does what it's supposed to do - simulate. This is a game I let run in the background once I've built up my team, which is something I really like doing with any simulation game. What I thought is cool about this game is that , the stats do matter and will effect your team, the front office you have also effects your team too. This game is really detailed when it comes to what actually effects your team and how the simulation runs. Sometimes, even if you build up this monster, stacked forward team, but lack depth, experienced defence and a reliable goalie, your team won't simlate as you expect - which is really nice. On top of all this, experience does play a HUGE factor when it comes to simulating and playoffs. If you run with a team that is all rookies, your team will not simulate well because they don't have experience nor do they have experienced players around them. That goes with the playoffs too, if your team is inexperienced in the playoffs you won't go deep until your players gain enough experience.I think the only negative I see are is the salary cap does not move. But it can be raised video EHM Assistant, which does wonders if you want to raise salary cap like the real NHL. Otherwise, amazing game would recommend!"
